      _see_] _bee_ MS.
    60. _wyght_] _wyttht_ MS.]

[Headnote: THE KING ASKS TORRENT TO FIGHT A GREEK GIANT.]

(6)

  [Sidenote:
  and asks him if, for her sake, heaEuro(TM)ll fight]

  Torrent sayd: aEuro~Be Marry dere,
  And I were off armyse clere,                   f. 77a.
    Yowr Dowghttyr me leve were.aEuro(TM)
  The kyng seyd: aEuro~Yf yt be soo,
  Ore VII yere be a-go,                                   65
    More schaAEsAEs we here:
  Durst thow, for my dowghttyr sake,
  A poynt of armys for to take
    W{i}t{h}-owt helpe of fere?aEuro(TM)
  Than seyd Torrant: aEuro~So god me sped,                     70
  W{i}t{h} anny man~ that syttythe on stede
    Other far ore nere!aEuro(TM)

    [Linenotes:
    61. _Marry_] _e_ corrected into _y_.
    65. _a-go_] _a gone_, _ne_ struck out,A MS.]

