  aEuro~Hedes and helmys ther was,
  I telle E�ow withowttene lese,
  Many layde {one the gresse},
  And many brode schelde.aEuro(TM)

p. 42, l. 1181. _For tynding of his hand_ = for fear of (=A _for_) the
beating (blows) of his hand. Schoolboy slang still keeps the word aEuro(TM)_to
tund_aEuro(TM) = to beat with something flat.--HALL.

p. 42, l. 1193. On this expression Skeat treats in _Notes to P. Pl._,
