  aEuro~He wold haue a draught, aplight.aEuro(TM)

p. 59, l. 1676. After _was_, _sent_ may have been dropped.

p. 59, l. 1692. _For his love_, i.e. aEuro~As his sweetheart.aEuro(TM)

p. 60, l. 1714. Cf. _Ipomadon_, l. 52:

  aEuro~Begge he wex of bonne and blode.aEuro(TM)

_Ib._ l. 1763:

  aEuro~Ryghtte bygge of bone and blode.aEuro(TM)

p. 60, l. 1722: aEuro~All his men agreed with him,aEuro(TM) viz. that this was the
